{
  "page": "Illyrio's chests",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p><b>Illyrio's chests</b> are six <a href=\"/index.php/Oak\" title=\"Oak\">oaken</a> chests with <a href=\"/index.php/Iron\" title=\"Iron\">iron</a> hasps belonging to <a href=\"/index.php/Illyrio_Mopatis\" title=\"Illyrio Mopatis\">Illyrio Mopatis</a>. Illyrio brings them with him from <a href=\"/index.php/Illyrio%27s_manse\" title=\"Illyrio&#39;s manse\">his manse</a> in <a href=\"/index.php/Pentos\" title=\"Pentos\">Pentos</a> when he travels by litter with <a href=\"/index.php/Tyrion_Lannister\" title=\"Tyrion Lannister\">Tyrion Lannister</a> to rendezvous with <a href=\"/index.php/Haldon_Halfmaester\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Haldon Halfmaester\">Haldon Halfmaester</a> and Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Rolly_Duckfield\" title=\"Rolly Duckfield\">Rolly Duckfield</a> in the <a href=\"/index.php/Velvet_Hills\" title=\"Velvet Hills\">Velvet Hills</a> near <a href=\"/index.php/Ghoyan_Drohe\" title=\"Ghoyan Drohe\">Ghoyan Drohe</a>. Haldon is expecting the chests.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd8.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd8.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Contents\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Contents</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Recent_Events\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Recent Events</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#A_Dance_with_Dragons\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\"><i>A Dance with Dragons</i></span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#Quotes\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Quotes</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#References_and_Notes\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References and Notes</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Contents\">Contents</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Illyrio%27s_chests&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Contents\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>According to Illyrio, there is some candied ginger in one of the chests.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd8.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd8.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> According to Rolly Duckfield, they contain <a href=\"/index.php/Armor\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Armor\">armor</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd8.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd8.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> Haldon notes there is also clothing in the chests — court clothes for all of <a href=\"/index.php/Griff\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Griff\">Griff</a>'s party, including fine woollens, velvets, and <a href=\"/index.php/Silk\" title=\"Silk\">silken</a> cloaks.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd8.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd8.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> He adds that the chests contain suitable gifts for Queen <a href=\"/index.php/Daenerys_Targaryen\" title=\"Daenerys Targaryen\">Daenerys Targaryen</a>, provided by Illyrio.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd8.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd8.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> One of the chests is packed with child's clothing, musty but well made.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd14.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd14.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> The chests also contain purses of <a href=\"/index.php/Silver\" title=\"Silver\">silver</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd22.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd22.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>It is not known what else the chests contain. They are not too heavy, as Duck is able to shift them easily on one shoulder.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd8.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd8.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Recent_Events\">Recent Events</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Illyrio%27s_chests&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Recent Events\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"A_Dance_with_Dragons\"><i>A Dance with Dragons</i></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Illyrio%27s_chests&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: A Dance with Dragons\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>In the Velvet Hills, Illyrio and Tyrion meet Haldon Halfmaester and Ser Rolly Duckfield, who take on Tyrion, supplies from Illyrio, and the six oaken chests. Haldon believes Illyrio's baggage <a href=\"/index.php/Mule\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Mule\">mules</a> would be too slow, so has Duck shift them to three <a href=\"/index.php/Horse\" title=\"Horse\">pack horses</a>. Before they depart, Illyrio tells them that there is a gift for <a href=\"/index.php/Young_Griff\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Young Griff\">Young Griff</a> in one of the chests, some candied ginger.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd8.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-6\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd8.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>When they halt for supper, Tyrion questions Duck and Haldon as to the contents of the chests. He tells them that he thought they contained <a href=\"/index.php/Gold\" title=\"Gold\">gold</a> for the <a href=\"/index.php/Golden_Company\" title=\"Golden Company\">Golden Company</a>, but after seeing Duck hoist a chest onto one shoulder, he realized that if it were full of <a href=\"/index.php/Coin\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Coin\">coin</a>, he could never have lifted it so easily. Duck and Haldon tell him that the chests contain armor and fine clothing, as well as gifts for Queen Daenaerys.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd8.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-7\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd8.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>The three reach the <a href=\"/index.php/Little_Rhoyne\" title=\"Little Rhoyne\">Little Rhoyne</a> at <a href=\"/index.php/Ghoyan_Drohe\" title=\"Ghoyan Drohe\">Ghoyan Drohe</a>, where a <a href=\"/index.php/Poleboat\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Poleboat\">poleboat</a>, the <i><a href=\"/index.php/Shy_Maid\" title=\"Shy Maid\">Shy Maid</a></i>, is waiting for them. The chests are stored on the poleboat.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd8.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-8\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd8.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> Later on the <i>Shy Maid</i>, <a href=\"/index.php/Septa\" title=\"Septa\">Septa</a> <a href=\"/index.php/Lemore\" title=\"Lemore\">Lemore</a> takes child's clothing from one of the chests, and uses them to make an outfit of motley for Tyrion.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd14.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd14.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>At <a href=\"/index.php/Selhorys\" title=\"Selhorys\">Selhorys</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Jon_Connington\" title=\"Jon Connington\">Jon Connington</a> sends Haldon and Tyrion ashore to learn news and rumors concerning Daenerys Targaryen. Griff gives them each a purse of silver from Illyrio's chests, to loosen tongues.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd22.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd22.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>After meeting with the Golden Company in <a href=\"/index.php/Volon_Therys\" title=\"Volon Therys\">Volon Therys</a>, Jon Connington tells Haldon to ride back to the <i>Shy Maid</i> and return with Illyrio's chests.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd24.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd24.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Not long afterwards, the Golden Company <a href=\"/index.php/Landing_of_the_Golden_Company\" title=\"Landing of the Golden Company\">land in Westeros</a> in multiple parties.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd61.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd61.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup> Illyrio's chests may be with Jon Connington's party, or one of the others.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Quotes\">Quotes</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Illyrio%27s_chests&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Quotes\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>You have some chests for us?<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd8.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-9\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd8.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;<a href=\"/index.php/Haldon\" title=\"Haldon\">Haldon</a>, to <a href=\"/index.php/Illyrio_Mopatis\" title=\"Illyrio Mopatis\">Illyrio Mopatis</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p><a href=\"/index.php/Gold\" title=\"Gold\">Gold</a> for the <a href=\"/index.php/Golden_Company\" title=\"Golden Company\">Golden Company</a>, I thought at first, until I saw Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Rolly_Duckfield\" title=\"Rolly Duckfield\">Rolly</a> hoist a chest onto one shoulder. if it were full of <a href=\"/index.php/Coin\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Coin\">coin</a>, he could never have lifted it so easily.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd8.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-10\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd8.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;<a href=\"/index.php/Tyrion_Lannister\" title=\"Tyrion Lannister\">Tyrion Lannister</a>, to <a href=\"/index.php/Haldon\" title=\"Haldon\">Haldon</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>Court clothes, for all our party. Fine woollens, velvets, <a href=\"/index.php/Silk\" title=\"Silk\">silken</a> cloaks. One does not come before <a href=\"/index.php/Daenerys_Targaryen\" title=\"Daenerys Targaryen\">a queen</a> looking shabby... or empty handed. The <a href=\"/index.php/Magister\" title=\"Magister\">magister</a> has been kind enough to provide us with suitable gifts.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd8.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-11\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd8.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;<a href=\"/index.php/Haldon\" title=\"Haldon\">Haldon</a>, to <a href=\"/index.php/Tyrion_Lannister\" title=\"Tyrion Lannister\">Tyrion Lannister</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>Ride back to the <i><a href=\"/index.php/Shy_Maid\" title=\"Shy Maid\">Shy Maid</a></i> and return with Lady <a href=\"/index.php/Lemore\" title=\"Lemore\">Lemore</a> and Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Rolly_Duckfield\" title=\"Rolly Duckfield\">Rolly</a>. We'll need <a href=\"/index.php/Illyrio_Mopatis\" title=\"Illyrio Mopatis\">Illyrio's</a> chests as well. All the <a href=\"/index.php/Coin\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Coin\">coin</a>, and the <a href=\"/index.php/Armor\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Armor\">armor</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd24.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd24.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;<a href=\"/index.php/Jon_Connington\" title=\"Jon Connington\">Jon Connington</a>, to <a href=\"/index.php/Haldon\" title=\"Haldon\">Haldon</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References_and_Notes\">References and Notes</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Illyrio%27s_chests&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: References and Notes\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-Radwd8.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\